Yes, the district will be providing continued learning through Microsoft Teams, Google Classroom or paper packets. If your student is using a district issued Chromebook these online platforms will be available after logging in. If your student is using a personal device, they can access these resources through Clever. Students without a device or internet can obtain the necessary items during our various distributions (see below). To log into a Chromebook your student will need to know their email address (studentid#@qsd.wednet.edu) and password (YYMMDD of their birthdate). 

Will  Chromebooks and Hotspots be  available  to  checkout?  
 Yes, Chromebooks and hotspots will be available district wide and have already been distributed to Quincy High School and Quincy Middle School students. If your high school or middle school student did not receive a device and is in need please call their school directly to arrange pickup. Quantities are limited so please do so as soon as possible. 

If your student is in elementary school, distribution of Chromebooks will take place at your student’s school April 27th from 10:30 AM to 12:30 PM, April 28th from 10:30 AM to 12:30 PM and April 28th from 5:30 PM to 7:30 PM. Distribution of hotspots for elementary students is tentatively scheduled for the week of May 3rd. Information about elementary student hotspot distribution will be sent out via Remind and other district communication methods. 

